After 600 Days, Gaza Still Bleeds

To the People of Gaza

Your resilience is unmatched. You have refused to abandon your land despite unimaginable suffering. Your courage in sharing your reality—your stories, your loss, your truth—is an act of resistance in itself. This is not about seeking pity, but about exposing what Israel tries to hide: a genocide, live-streamed in real time. The world must see what it means to survive under occupation, under siege, under silence.

To the Doctors and Aid Workers

You walk into the fire with nothing but your humanity. You risk your lives to save others, to treat the wounded, to deliver food, water, and dignity. You are the beating heart of hope amid destruction. Thank you for your bravery.

To the Truth Tellers and the Brave

Independent journalists, charity workers, protest organizers, activists, artists, and all who raise their voices—you are the light cutting through the fog of propaganda. Every donation, every protest, every speech, every act of defiance matters. To the politicians who speak truth to power, to the business owners who invest in justice, to the artists who risk their careers: your stand is not forgotten.

For 600 days, Gaza has been a graveyard for the world’s conscience. The world turned a blind eye—but now the truth is undeniable.

Those who once stood with the so-called “democracy” and “moral army” are witnessing the reality: ethnic cleansing, war crimes, terrorism wrapped in political rhetoric.

Trump and Netanyahu are not defending—they are destroying. This is not about security; it is about annexation, about building a so-called "Greater Israel" through acts of cowardice, cruelty, and inhumanity.

How can a nation claim greatness while burying children under rubble?

To the People of Dignity and Humanity

You are the fire that keeps our hope alive. May your courage fuel the fight for a free Palestine. One day, history will remember who stood on the side of justice, and who looked away.

From the ashes of Gaza, may freedom rise.
